        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-8">
          <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5" style="border-left: 3px solid #3b82f6;">
            <h4 class="font-semibold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-sm mb-2">NIST AI RMF 1.0</h4>
            <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-faint)] mb-2">January 2023 &middot; US Federal &middot; Voluntary</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">Four core functions: GOVERN, MAP, MEASURE, MANAGE. Seven properties of trustworthy AI. Increasingly referenced as compliance safe harbor.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5" style="border-left: 3px solid #06b6d4;">
            <h4 class="font-semibold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-sm mb-2">UNESCO AI Ethics</h4>
            <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-faint)] mb-2">November 2021 &middot; 194 member states &middot; Voluntary</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">First global normative instrument on AI ethics. 10 core principles, 11 policy areas. Universal adoption but no enforcement mechanism.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5" style="border-left: 3px solid #8b5cf6;">
            <h4 class="font-semibold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-sm mb-2">UNESCO Neurotechnology Ethics</h4>
            <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-faint)] mb-2">November 12, 2025 &middot; Global &middot; Voluntary</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">Directly addresses devices that read and write neural data. The closest international instrument to what QIF proposes at the technical level.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5" style="border-left: 3px solid #10b981;">
            <h4 class="font-semibold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-sm mb-2">EU AI Act</h4>
            <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-faint)] mb-2">August 2024 &middot; EU &middot; <strong>Binding</strong></p>
            <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">First comprehensive AI law. Risk tiers: Unacceptable (banned), High (conformity assessment), Limited (transparency), Minimal. Neural interfaces with AI likely classified as high-risk. Penalties up to 7% of global revenue.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5" style="border-left: 3px solid #f59e0b;">
            <h4 class="font-semibold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-sm mb-2">Council of Europe Convention</h4>
            <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-faint)] mb-2">Opened for signature September 5, 2024 &middot; EU + additional countries &middot; <strong>Binding treaty</strong></p>
            <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">First legally binding international AI treaty. Requires human rights safeguards, procedural transparency, discrimination prevention, and remedy for affected persons.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5" style="border-left: 3px solid #ef4444;">
            <h4 class="font-semibold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-sm mb-2">FDA SaMD / PCCP</h4>
            <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-faint)] mb-2">Ongoing &middot; US &middot; <strong>Binding</strong></p>
            <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">Predetermined Change Control Plan: AI medical devices can adapt within pre-specified guardrails without new regulatory submissions. Directly applicable to adaptive BCIs.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="glass rounded-xl p-6 mb-6" style="border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent-tertiary);">
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">
            <strong class="text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">Why this matters for architecture:</strong> Policy says &ldquo;AI should be transparent.&rdquo; The question is whether a technical framework can operationalize that as an architectural constraint &mdash; not a suggestion, but a requirement enforced by the system itself. QIF proposes that it can, through mandatory audit logging, amplitude bounds, and consent gates. Whether this approach is sufficient is an open question requiring independent validation.
